Its the year 2102. You are on the top of the m.i.s.a. tower, more specific, in the Gallery known as "the Junkyard". In 2050 the world started to recycle everything, so there was no junk of any kind left by 2080. That made junk, which was found in the dephts of the ocean or woods and swamps, extremly valuable to the collector who has everything else. Your first adress would be "the Junkyard", established in 2085 the Gallery sells only high class junk. Of course valuable stuff always lures some criminals. But the security team has already found out and locked the escalators. Terrorists: Fight off the security team and watch out for your hostages, they are your only way out know! Counter-Terrorists: Your first objective is to rescue the hostages. As for the intruders ...shoot on sight! - made for Counter-Strike: Source - cubemaps - small 3d skybox - HUD - NAV - Custom Textures - 32 Playerspawns - Ventsystem - 4 Hostages to rescue - All content is packed into BSP Please see the "credits" Box on the right side. If I forgot to add someone, contact me. I will fix it right away. Well, what to say. This is my entry for the Junkyard Contest and my second released map. It was made on 3.5 weekends consuming lots of Red Bull and Doctor Who. And its actually the first time I got the HUD to work, so yay for that. The idea is kind of a longshot, but I didn't wanted to do just a "simple" junkyard. So thats what I came up with, I hope you like it. As always, feedback is very welcome. Please don't decompile. If you need anything or want to know something about the map, PM me or post a comment. Thank you.

My second release, three weeks in the making (most of that because it kept crashing or hanging during the compile), I present cs_texture_villa!

I wanted to try my hand at making a decent cs map ^^; there're four hossies that need saving from the terrorist stronghold, and two extraction points to choose from. The map supports upto 42 players, has two CT and one T spawn, and the rooves are accessible from multiple points across the map. 

If you fancy it, it should also be good for GG as well!

The Radar - I did try to embed it in the BSP but it doesn't seem to be working that way; if someone would like to look at the BSP and tell me what I'm doing wrong, that'd be great; for now, it's included as seperate files.

Thanks to SmmS for the encouragement & positive feedback from my previous map, gg_hextower - give it a look, it plays quite well!

How to install map: put the cs_terroristownage in Steam\steamapps\yourusername\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps


Remember to play as counter terrorist!


When you are in counter strike source menu, press Create Server and set Include bots on and set bot limit to 6 + in the Game Section set maxplayers to 7 and disable enemy weapons in the next section!

When you are in the server open console (if you dont have console enabled then right click steam icon select library 
then right click counter strike source and select properties then click Set Launch Options... and write this in: -console)

put in console these: mp_limitteams 6 and mp_autoteambalance 0


enjoy the map! :D

This is the first version of cs_tenacity. There will be bugs, there will be newbie techniques. Provide constructive, helpful criticism and help me get better.

cs_tenacity was a project I began working on once I discovered it would be physically impossible to compile aim_opposition on Normal in VVIS. It was a culmination of interesting concepts that I pooled together into a Complex-Themed Map. Things like controllable Gates, Shutters on Windows, Cameras, and Swining Targets are the sort of things you can expect to find in this map. The 2 lights in the dark corridor were supposed to be dynamic, but they lagged the map badly.

This map was made entirely by me, Nexolate. Special Thanks go out to Woo, who taught me the basics of Portalling, and for the inspirational maps he makes. You may not copy, edit or redistribute this Map without my explicit permission.

Enjoy.

EDIT: 32 Player Version released.

Original Author: [D*H] ~ Kon$olE Mapper: Silent Ricochet Custom Textures: Shiroko Custom Bumpmapping: Silent Ricochet Summary: A moderately medium sized map. Very well optimized, should run well on almost any semi-decent platform. I get a constant 100+FPS on a 4 year old machine. The map has seen a huge change since it's last release, mostly texture aligning, got rid of some brush clutter, soundscapes, a new 3d skybox, and bumpmaps for VALVe textures. This comes with a NAV file as well including info_nodes and other entities of that sort to help the hostages and bots navigate the map better. Have fun :)
Change Log: Version 3.0 Additions -Optimized the hell out of the map (nodraw plays a huge part) -Added numerous soundscapes (for better reverb and sound effects). -Added more Cubemaps (for more accurately shown reflections) -Added step in front of Podium -Added more money props, desk and office chair to left hostage room -Added tons of Info_nodes and info_node_climbs -Added button that plays church music -Added Powerbox and buttons in basement -Added immense 3d skybox -Added several bumpmaps to 3-4 textures to correct visual errors and add realism Changes/Fixes -Fixed Cubemaps that were being displayed from the floor below/above -Fixed Texture mis-alignments -Fixed Incorrect spawn points -Fixed color and brightness of basement lights -Fixed Mis-aligned brushes -Fixed some mis-shaped brushes effecting gameplay and lighting -Improved brush work of podium, grass, and walls. -Changed complicated objects to func_detail for a raise in performance -Changed the directions terrorists were facing when spawning -Deleted a few ambient generics that didn't play a significant role -Deleted insignificant brushes that created clutter and dropped performance -Other small changes and fixes that I forgot and really don't matter
Version 2.0 Additions -Optimized greatly, saving 40+FPS since last version -Added 3d Skybox -Added Parking Lot -Added green window lighting effects -Added Small plants and other props -Added a few decals -Added More cubemaps -Added Ambient sounds -Added ramps on most entrances (realism sakes) -Added Front doors (doors?! holy crap really?1!?) Changes/Fixes -Fixed cubemaps -Fixed Water rendering -Fixed small cracks in ceiling, walls, and ground -Improved the Pews -Made ground, windows, walls, and other miscellaneous brushes thinner (realism sakes) -Changed ropes from brushes to move ropes with invis ladder textures -Changed texture of outside wall -Changed lighting in basement, nixed a few lights to make it darker -Changed front gate from crappy brush to props -Changed health of all breakable brushes (realism) -Re-built and edited nav file greatly improving efficiency of Bot gameplay -Re-arranged static props for better gameplay and hiding spots. -Some small other fixes and changes

TITLE**: CS:S Map - cs_SynStreets - small, dark, urban CS:S combat map.
AUTHOR**: Flatline_Construct
E-MAIL**: flatline_construct@hotmail.co.uk
WEBSITE: XFIRE - flatlineconstruct

FILENAME: cs_synstreets.bsp
FILESIZE: 3.88 MB
Max players : 24
DATE RELEASED: 16th February 2007

CREDITS**: All me!! using Hl2/CS:S content provided by valve!

INSTALLATION INSTRUCTIONS**: Just put the map in your CS:S folder! aka \Valve\Steam\SteamApps\*your account*\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps

DESCRIPTION**: This is a small dark combat map for CS:S set in an urban crossroads, slight cyberpunk elements, intended for all weapons except sniper rifles.

COMMENTS: I drew from syndicate and typical cyberpunk elements to create this level, but at the same time wanted to keep it simple and in keeping with CS:S, also I always find myself buying the night vision goggles for no reason, and on this map they're quite usefull.

This is my first public release!

This is my second major map final release to the public.  I have made many more, though this is the one that owned up to my level of standard for an official release.  cs_symphony has been in development for 10 months.  It was started after the success of my first major map release, cs_kismayo and de_kismayo.

     cs_symphony is a smaller map than cs_kismayo, but still has the same level of detail and finely tuned gameplay that you would expect.  It is loosely modeled after the music building on Capital University's campus in Columbus Ohio.

     HDR was not added to this map because it acted glitchy when applied.  The map really looks great without it anyway.  Placenames are included.

     Please enjoy the map.  If you have any comments or concerns of any kind, feel free to email me at jazzbassking@hotmail.com or im me on AIM, sn: OreoCookieSP.

     Have Fun,
     Oreo

Installation:
Assuming you have steam on C: the default location will be
C:\Program Files(x86)\Steam\steamapps\yoursteamid\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps
Place all 3 files (.nav .bsp .txt) in there.

Special thanks to all who have tested this map through its various stages of development.

Any feedback would be much appreciated and of course if you have any problems be sure to let me know :) 

Please do not decompile or Re-release without permission.

MAP NAME: cs_subway_v1
BSP FILESIZE: 26 MB (about 9 MB zipped) 
DATE RELEASED: January 22th, 2007 
PRODUCTION LENGTH: 1.5 months 
AUTHOR: C.M. Allen(cm_allen1@yahoo.com) 
SPAWNPOINTS: 20 terrorist, 20 counter-terrorist, 40 total. 

This is a recreation of 
The Rogue Spear: Urban Operations level called the London Subway.  I also added some Vents to it, since everyone loves going through vents.

I tried doing a good job of Optimizing ,Nav Tuning, and fixing snags with clipping, but I know I still have lots to learn about mapping including lighting, and etc.  So I would like to have some feedback on things to work on.

A few things that I have in progress and in mind to work on are:

More Detail- Subway Signs and Banners
             Dirt, Grime, and Other details to make it more "used looking"
             Adding Props, to fill out level.
             Creating Custom Textures for walls to break up that sameness.

Better Lighting
Better Optimizing
Better Nav Tuning

Thanks and enjoy
